sections.heading: assessor in counties over 200,000 population; deputies
sections.text: In counties having a population of over two hundred thousand, the county assessor shall have two chief deputies, a chief field deputy and a chief office deputy.SourceLaws 1903, c. 73, ยง 22, p. 392;Laws 1905, c. 110, ยง 1, p. 509;Laws 1909, c. 111
